Former Imo State Governor, Ikedi Ohakim, yesterday, narrated how a bulletproof vehicle saved him after an attack by heavily armed gunmen who killed four of his police escorts.
  
Ohakim’s convoy was ambushed on Monday night at Oriagu in Ehime Mbano Local Council of Imo State.
 
He said even when his own driver managed to escape from the scene, the assailants pursued his vehicle.
 
Narrating the incident, the former governor said: “We were driving between Isiala Mbano and Ehime Mbano. These people blocked us at a place called Umualumaku. 